1. Definitions

The Kernel: The Successional Wave Architecture, 900-unit manifold, and associated recursive logic.

The Architect: Travis Raymond-Charlie Stone.

Individual Use: Non-commercial, peer-to-peer, or educational use.

Centralized Exploitation: Any use by an entity with an annual revenue exceeding $1M or any government/corporate body using the Kernel for centralized ledger/transactional control.

2. Permissions

Verification: Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person to run, test, and verify the Kernel for the purpose of mathematical and scientific validation.

Peer-to-Peer: Individual users may utilize the Kernel for "Server-Zero" local computation and decentralized mesh communication without royalty.

3. Restrictions (The Sovereign Clause)

No Centralized Re-branding: The Kernel may not be integrated into proprietary closed-source systems without the express written consent of the Architect.

Dividend Requirement: Entities engaged in Centralized Exploitation must negotiate a "Stability Dividend" (royalty) to be paid into the Stoneconomics distribution engine.

Attribution: All copies or substantial portions of the Software must include the original copyright notice: "Copyright 2026 Travis Raymond-Charlie Stone. Riemann-Verified Logic."

4. Termination

Any attempt to use the Kernel to facilitate data harvesting, centralized surveillance, or logical corruption (Bifurcation) automatically terminates this license for the offending party.
